{"key":"post-15814371","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15814371</id>\n<content>We soak to slowly hydrate the grains so they don't burst in the pressure cooker from expanding too fast.&amp;nbsp; It's not absolutely necessary, but results are better with the soak.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The old method was to simply add grains and water to the jar and then pressure cook.&amp;nbsp; The rinse, soak, boil, strain method is an evolution of that into something that's a bit more effort, but worth it in added performance.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15814413</next>\n<prev>15814300</prev>\n<first>15814300</first>\n<last>15814472</last>\n<when>1329349449</when>\n<utime>02/16/12 01:44 AM</utime>\n</post>"}